description: This 2-week camp offered by Fairfax County Parks provides a fun and engaging experience for participants. Advance registration is required as space is limited. Refunds or credits for missed days are not available for work, vacation, sick days, or other non-emergency reasons. Refunds for Extended Care are given in full if requested within 14 days in advance of the camp session start date. Refunds within 14 days of the camp session start date are only approved for specific reasons.

name: Baseball Beginners Camp
description: In this one-day camp, kids aged 6-13 years will engage in a variety of hands-on projects, creating crafts inspired by baseball. With safety and fun as a guide, this camp will introduce skills such as throwing, catching, and more.

name: Coding & Robo Fun
description: Develop and share computer programs that combine multimedia elements to create interactive stories, animations, games, music, and art. Bring creations to life through coding and robotics. For ages 6-12.

name: Chess Camp Workshop
description: This Silver Knights camp teaches both fundamentals and advanced skills in a fun atmosphere. Campers learn the great strategy game to explore STEM concepts.

camp: Rec Center Music and Tech Camp
name: Super Hero Doodles
description: This one-day camp is designed for advanced players looking to sharpen their skills in pitching, hitting, baserunning, fielding, and strategy, as well as for beginners who want to learn the game and sportsmanship. Campers will learn the rules, openings, tactics, strategy, and endgames while playing games. The camp includes daily scrimmages, trivia contests, and instruction sessions. Campers should bring a swimsuit and towel for an afternoon swim break. Suitable for ages 5 ½ - 12 years.

name: Super-Sized Collages, Capes, and Masks
description: Participants will engage in creating super-sized collages, capes, and masks while taking outdoor breaks. The program aims to foster creativity and artistic expression in a fun and interactive outdoor setting.

camp: Nature Camps ACTion! Pop Star Spotlight B2R DJ Camp
name: Animals: Zoology Fun
description: Performers channel their favorite pop stars like Taylor Swift, Katy Perry, and the Jonas Brothers. Take center stage in this crash course to the world of DJing. Led by professional DJs, students explore the woods, creeks, and ponds as we look for all sorts of critters. Learn about the animal kingdom and have fun in this exciting program.

name: Band on the Instrument
description: Campers will participate in rock climbing, meet professional musicians, and receive coaching to learn, record, and perform at least two songs by the end of the week. The program also includes activities such as exploring wildlife, fishing, and hiking. Different themes are featured each week, and kids get to perform in a magical setting.

camp: Fairfax County Park Authority Summer Camps
name: Green Locations
description: Join us at Riverbend Park for the Green Locations program where you will learn about teamwork, nature, and environmental conservation. This program is open to all levels of experience, and family and friends are welcome to enjoy a mini-performance on Friday.

name: Chess Camp
description: Campers enjoy guided nature hikes, crafts, and fishing. Shaded trails and lakefronts are perfect settings for exploring creatures and plants that live in our streams, lakes, and forests. Campers also learn chess skills as they master techniques and draw popular characters like Gudetame (Lazy Egg Yolk) and Totoro. This Silver Knights Chess Camp has taught this strategy game for ages 6-13 years. Campers will even paint their own anime-style self-portraits.

name: BandLab Music Production Program
description: Participants will explore hidden woodland, stream, and pond habitats while learning about aquatic life investigations and popular music production using BandLab. Campers will craft songs through loops, beats, and samples in this engaging program.

location.address: Hidden Woodland, Stream, and Pond Habitats

name: Peter Pan Mini-Musical Camp
description: Join us for a one-week journey through Neverland in our modern mini-musical twist on 'Peter Pan'. Young performers at all levels of experience are welcome to participate in this exciting camp.

name: Explore Your World!
description: Join Camprichment to explore visiting, working, or living around the world. Play geography games, develop travel plans and inspiration boards. Learn about traveling careers.

camp: Spark Business Academy Sports Business Camp
name: Fashion Sketching and Business
description: This program combines the art of fashion sketching with basic business skills. Participants will learn how to create fashion sketches and explore the process of selling them for profit. Additionally, campers will study wildlife data techniques to design outfits inspired by parkland wildlife. They will also engage in marketing activities, estimate profits, and experiment with creating marketing flyers. Repeat campers will have the opportunity to create a unique tote bag. The program offers various games and activities for enjoyment.

name: Flight Academy
description: As a Mad Science flight cadet, you will take a nosedive into the world of aerodynamics. Build your own kite, test stunt planes, and watch as we launch.

name: Messiest Science Experiments & Taylor-inspired Crafts
description: Campers will learn dances, create messy science experiments, and Taylor Swift-inspired crafts. The week will end with a foam, slime, and potions experience. This hands-on camp is designed for children aged 5-12 years.

name: Science Camp: Magic Sand, Foam, Slime, and Potions
description: Immerse your child into the enchanting realm of science as we unravel the secrets of magic sand, foam, slime, and potions. Concoct elixirs that magically change color, create your own bouncy balls, and whip up some homemade PopR with Kidcreate. This camp is designed to engage curious minds in a hands-on exploration of science.

name: Science Explorers Camp
description: Science Explorers Camp at Spring Break at Frying Pan Farm Park offers a unique experience for children aged 8-12. Participants will engage in hands-on scientific experiments that combine creativity and exploration. The camp aims to immerse children in scientific concepts while fostering a love for experimentation. Throughout the week, campers will explore history, farm animals, crops, gardening, wagon rides, and other nature activities.

location.address: Frying Pan Farm Park, [Full Address Here]

name: Spring Break on the Farm
description: Learn about the newest farm babies and other animals through daily farm visits. Activities also include hikes, crafts, and games. This camp meets at Old Floris Schoolhouse.

name: Ultimate Music Experience
description: Learn Now Music introduces campers to a variety of musical instruments and concepts including piano, guitar, violin, drums, voice, and movement. Campers participate in musical games, crafts, and musical activities.

camp: Second Sunday Craft Camp Adventure at the Woodlands
name: Zootastic Art Camp
description: Participants will focus on a variety of different field activities each day with SMUV Sports Zoo-Tastic Art Camp including capture the flag, kickball, and soccer. Campers will learn new techniques to sculpt 3D clay animals.

camp: Beyond Soccer and Coach Rich Basketball Camp
name: Baseball Beginners Camp with Brazilian Soccer Techniques
description: BeyondSoccer's Baseball Beginners Camp combines authentic Brazilian soccer techniques with fundamental baseball skills. The camp focuses on teaching skills such as throwing, catching, fielding, hitting, and baserunning in a fun and safe environment. Participants will experience transformative experiences while enjoying a week of engaging activities.

name: Soccer
description: Join Baroody Sports for games teaching and advanced skills in a fun atmosphere. Campers develop well-rounded soccer skills leading up to playing small-sided soccer. Enjoy daily scrimmages, trivia contests, and instruction outdoors, rain or shine.

name: Creative Skills Camp
description: Creative Skills Camp offers a wide variety of activities for children aged 6-13. It is a unique camp focusing on soccer and games, with soccer at its core. Through its innovative approach, campers will develop their skills in a fun and engaging environment.

camp: Rec Center Music and Tech Camp
name: Fencing Camp
description: In this action-packed camp, campers will participate in a variety of sports after lunch including soccer, kickball, and capture the flag. The camp includes an afternoon swim break. Join us for an exciting week of fencing with Fairfax Fencers.

name: Fencing Camp
description: Join us for a week-long Fencing Camp where you will learn etiquette and safety in all three fencing disciplines: foil, epee, and saber. Show off your skills at the end-of-the-week camp tournament.

name: Total Sports Camp
description: Total Sports Camp offers a high-energy program for children aged 6 to 13. Participants will engage in a variety of sports such as basketball, flag football, soccer, and track. The day includes outdoor activities, story time related to daily science themes, free reading, exploration, and journal entries. Participants are required to bring a snack, water bottle, lunch, swimsuit, 2 towels, change of clothes, and sunscreen. Camp does not run on June 19 and July 4.

name: Battle of the Bots Camp
description: Get ready for an action-packed adventure in robotics with iCode’s Battle of the Bots camp. Campers will dive into the fascinating world of VEX, experiencing the thrill of signing, building, programming, and controlling their robots.

name: STEM Coding Camp
description: Stemtree campers will code in either Python or Scratch based on their grade levels. Python is one of the highly visual programming languages suitable for younger students. Scratch is a highly visual programming language suitable for beginners.

name: Junior ROCS
description: Explore nature’s wonders throughout an exciting week. Each day presents new opportunities, from kayaking to white water rafting to hiking adventures and learning outdoor living skills.

camp: Rec Center Music and Tech Camp
name: Travel Mountain Biking Camp
description: Join Baroody Outside for an exhilarating week-long experience for young riders eager to master the art of mountain biking. From foundational skills to advanced techniques, this camp offers a comprehensive program to enhance your mountain biking abilities.

camp: Rec Center Music and Tech Camp
name: Tackling Intermediate Challenges
description: This program focuses on developing skills to tackle intermediate challenges in outdoor activities. Campers will receive comprehensive instruction on steering, shifting, hill climbing and descending, obstacle navigation, and more.

camp: Rec Center Music and Tech Camp
description: This Outdoor Camp program at nSpHill REC includes activities such as navigation, trail etiquette, bike maintenance, and safety. Participants will engage in outdoor adventures while learning important skills to navigate and enjoy the wilderness safely.

name: Baroody Outside
description: Baroody Outside offers a dynamic week at Chesapeake Bay for children aged 7-11 years. Campers will have the opportunity to explore freshwater ponds, rivers, lakes, and engage with the Native Animal Explorers. The program includes off-site experiences where kids can hike trails, wade in streams, and explore ponds, fostering a passion for outdoor exploration.

Campers will have the opportunity to explore nature and the wild at Green Locations. Each day offers a different adventure, including fishing, orienteering, catching, photographing, and releasing frogs, toads, tadpoles, hiking, creek exploration, and climbing. Campers will have the chance to observe native wildlife such as salamanders, lizards, turtles, crayfish, minnows, and more. They will be transported to various scenic spots for these activities.

name: Kayaking Adventure
description: Join us for an exciting kayaking adventure where campers will learn kayaking skills while exploring the native wildlife along waterways, ponds, and lakes. Campers will have the opportunity to get up close to the wildlife and enjoy the beauty of the outdoors.

camp: Fairfax County Park Authority Summer Camps
name: Fish & Explore
description: Fish & Explore takes campers to lakes, rivers, and the Chesapeake Bay to catch fish, learn water safety, and engage in swim clinics. A great camp for high-level swimmers.

name: Freshwater Fishing Fun Camp
description: Campers will gain knowledge and experience in freshwater fishing basics including casting, rigging, knot tying, selecting tackle and lures, and identifying fish. They will also enjoy out-of-pool games and activities. Participants will learn to wear lifejackets when in the water or on a boat. Prerequisite: Child must be able to swim 25 yards.

camp: Rec Center Music and Tech Camp
name: Responsible Angling Practices
description: Campers will gain the knowledge and skills necessary to become self-reliant anglers. The camp's focus is to foster a deep appreciation for the outdoors while equipping campers with the tools to enjoy fishing.

name: Pastel Camp
description: Campers will learn pastel drawing and techniques. The colorful, modern decorative design gives young artists an opportunity to create 3D objects that encourage mastery of clay techniques.

name: Creative Kids Art Workshop
description: Challenge your creative kids by introducing them to the world of pastels. Explore turing techniques to illustrate bees, an army of frogs, a striking owl, and more artistic critters. A guaranteed favorite summer tradition for every Young Rembrandts artist.

camp: nGREEN LOCATION CAMPS After School Program
name: Art Explorers Camp
description: Art Explorers Camp at Oakton Elementary School offers a creative and engaging program for children aged 6-14 years. Participants will have the opportunity to turn their drawings into small-scale models using soft bricks, not LEGO®. The camp includes activities such as building with soft bricks, exploring art mediums through craft projects, and creating wearable jewelry sets. Children will also have the chance to go outside and explore buildings in the surrounding area. At the end of the camp, each participant will take home a junior hard hat and sketch painting.

camp: Games & Swim Camp + Zoo-Tastic Art Camp
name: Art Exploration Camp
description: Art Exploration Camp offers a creative and fun environment for children to explore various art forms such as painting, paper arts, and sculpting. The emphasis is on fostering creativity, engaging in fun games, and nurturing a love for art. Participants are encouraged to bring a smock, snack, lunch, and drink. Swim time is included on June 19 and July 4.

name: FANtastic Art of Clay
description: Enjoy making top-requested projects in this FANtastic Art of Clay camp where your camper's favorite cartoon characters will come to life. Design and build cute puppy minions, Scooby, Olaf, and more using different types of clay. Transportation is included in the fee. No camp on July 4. Camps available the week of June 9 for non-FCPS participants.

name: Artistic Creations Camp
description: Join Kidcreate to design a 3D masterpiece that pops out right at you. Participants will learn terms and techniques while working on bobbleheads, crafting a 3D pet goldfish, designing with clay, and drawing their dream treehouse. Pack a nut-free lunch, snack, and drink daily.

name: Foundations of Pottery
description: Explore multiple techniques as they create drawings using a variety of different media including pencil, oil pastel, and watercolor. Pack a nut-free lunch and snack.

name: Myths & Legends Art Camp
description: Boys and girls aged 8-12 years will learn sewing basics, hand-building techniques, and machine operation to create sculptures, drawings, and paintings inspired by world myths and legends. This camp includes measuring, hand and machine techniques, maintenance, and machine operation. No pottery wheels are used in this camp.

camp: Rec Center Music and Tech Camp
name: Sewing: Donut & Cookie Pillow
description: This program offers participants the opportunity to learn how to sew and create adorable donut and cookie pillows. Participants will learn basic sewing techniques and create their own unique pillows to take home.

name: Truly Enchanted
description: Join Kidcreate for the Truly Enchanted Art Camp where kids will paint, sculpt with air-dry clay, and sing along to their favorite tunes while creating dazzling art pieces. This camp includes creating clay butterflies, magical bedroom doors, and Colombian rainforest creatures. Participants aged 5-12 years are welcome to join. Pack a nut-free lunch and snack.

name: Sewing Camp
description: Sewing Camp at Katydid Kids offers children aged 5 ½ to 12 years a creative experience with toys, crafts, games, music, and sewing activities. Participants will engage in sewing projects with provided kits including fabric, patterns, and notions. An additional supply fee of $35 is required. The camp runs from 9am to 4pm at Stenwood ES from 7/21 to 7/25 and at Wkfld/Moore from 7/28 to 8/1. For specific inquiries, contact 703-689-3104 or info@katydidkids.com.

name: Sweets and Serve Ware
description: Join Craftspace to explore different parts facts and stories about the animals through indoor. Join Mudskippers as we create sweet of our world through hands-on projects, creating and outdoor games, songs and puppetry. Bring treats and serve ware. We will also spend time baking, colorful art to display.

location.address: Old NEW! Wild Worlds Floris Schoolhouse

name: World Famous Paintings
description: This Young Rembrandts’ camp will focus on five different world-famous paintings, allowing campers to explore various art styles and techniques. Participants will have the opportunity to create their interpretations of these masterpieces while learning about the artists and historical context.

camp: Moonlit Wings Summer Camp: Peter Pan Mini-Musical
name: Wild about Animals Art Camp
description: Join us for an exciting art camp where you will discover animals and their different habitats through creating your own masterpiece. No experience is necessary for this camp. Please wear an old shirt or smock to class each day. A supply fee of $20 is due on the first day.

name: Animal Ambassadors
description: Go hiking to explore our native mammals, birds, fish, insects and reptiles in their habitats.

name: Farm Hand Camp
description: Explore life as a farm hand by milking cows or goats and tending to farm animals. Campers will learn why animals are important to our ecosystem through resident animal interactions, crafts, games, and activities. They will also explore the forest, pond, river, and participate in chores, games, and listen to guest speakers.

name: Farm Animals and Insects Exploration Camp
description: Explore the habits and biology of farm animals and insects at Frying Pan Farm Park through hikes, projects, and games. Discover the ancestors of our farm animals and the countless creatures living in the farm's surroundings.

camp: Second Sunday Craft Camp Adventure at the Woodlands
name: Eco Engineers Camp
description: Join our park naturalists as we search for inspiration from nature’s engineers - honeybees, beavers, birds, and plants. Test out different materials including goat milking and working. Experience life on a farm through activities.

name: Excavation Investigation
description: Excavation Investigation is a fun and educational summer camp where kids get to explore archaeology and excavation techniques. Participants will learn about different excavation tools, methods, and uncover hidden treasures while understanding the importance of preserving historical artifacts.

name: Survival Camp
description: Discover the secrets of soil, exploring archaeology, geology, and the critters that live beneath our feet! Learn the way to survive in the Northeast wilderness through challenging tasks and games. Daily nature walks, crafts, and experiments. Survivors will join each other in shelter building, water filtration, fire building, wilderness first aid, and fishing. Bring drink, snack, and lunch daily.

name: Forces of Nature Camp
description: Through experiments, campers will learn how weather impacts the earth, the role plants play as a natural force, and more.

camp: Fairfax County Park Authority Summer Camps
name: Insect Safari
description: Come on a safari and explore bugs and insects that inhabit our natural areas. Collect, examine and identify little creatures using magnifiers and microscopes.

name: Garden Sprouts Exploration
description: Learn about the important jobs of pollinators and decomposers through projects and scientific investigations. Camp is open to curious minds aged 4-6 years old who will explore nature through seek-and-find activities.

camp: Nature Camps ACTion! Pop Star Spotlight B2R DJ Camp
name: Junior Naturalist Camp
description: Campers will enjoy fishing, hiking, nature crafts, and spend the week with a naturalist learning games and boating lakeside. The camp includes swimming at Hidden Pond Nature Explorers to learn about the world around you and the various roles of time at our famous Water Mine Family Swimmin’ Hole. Study the park’s wildlife through data collection (dependent on weather/waterpark operation).

Habitat Exploration program for children aged 6-9 years old. Participants will engage in activities focused on exploring different habitats, learning about local wildlife, and environmental conservation.

camp: Second Sunday Craft Camp Adventure at the Woodlands
name: Hidden Treasure Pirate Camp
description: Join our pirate crew in search for natural treasures in the park. Make treasure chests, look for messages in bottles, find hidden treasure, and blast balloon cannon.

name: Nature Quest Jr.
description: Young nature explorers will enjoy a variety of activities focused on the skills needed to survive when Virginia was still a frontier. This program is designed for children aged 4-6 years old.

name: Future Scientists Exploration
description: Future scientists will explore the world of science, engineering, art, and innovation in this camp. Each day campers will be given a question or challenge for inspiration, and they will engage in lab experiments, hands-on fieldwork, wildlife observations, and outdoor adventures. Activities include hikes to the wetland, arts and crafts, games, animal encounters, and hands-on activities.

camp: Fairfax County Park Authority Summer Camps
name: Nature Exploration Camp
description: Join our naturalist on outdoor adventures and field studies in nature. Develop new skills to explore the wildlife through hands-on activities such as hikes, arts and crafts, and games. Participants will engage in activities like kayaking, fishing, and other outdoor studies. This camp is designed for serious nature lovers aged 9-13 years. Participants are required to bring lunch, drink, swimsuit, towel for daily swim, and be prepared for various outdoor activities. No camp on June 19 and July 4.

name: Women in the Woods ACTion!
description: Join our naturalist for an outdoor adventure as campers learn about skills the early settlers used. Explore improvisation, The Wizard of Oz, and more.

camp: Moonlit Wings Summer Camp: Peter Pan Mini-Musical
name: Young Performers Camp
description: Join Moonlit Wings Productions for the Young Performers Camp where young participants aged 7-14 will engage in fun activities such as drama games, character creation, talent shows, and more. Participants will develop important life skills, storytelling abilities, and outdoor survival skills. They will also have the opportunity to channel their favorite pop stars like Taylor Swift, Katy Perry, and the Jonas Brothers. All levels are welcome, and participants will work on teamwork and imagination. Family and friends can also enjoy activities like rock climbing, paddling, and fire building.

name: Applause! The Lion Queen
description: Join the Moonlit Wings Performing Arts Camp for an exciting two-week session where kids aged 7-14 will act in the original musical 'The Lion Queen,' a fresh take on a familiar favorite. Participants will have the opportunity to bring the magical Oz-themed musical 'ACTify! Disney’s Moana Jr.' to life, as well as shine in original scenes and skits.

camp: Explore Improvisation Camp: Disney's Moana Jr.
name: Disney's Moana Jr.
description: Join the Explore Improvisation Camp's Young Performers Camp for an exciting journey into the world of Disney's Moana Jr. This camp offers young performers the opportunity to engage in games, character creation, talent shows, and more, all while featuring beloved songs from the hit film. Participants will develop their imagination, storytelling skills, and teamwork as they embark on an adventure in Motunui and the Pacific. All levels are welcome, and family and friends can enjoy the final showcase.

name: Peter Pan Mini-Musical Camp
description: Join the Moonlit Wings One-Week Drama Camp for young performers aged 8-16. Dive into a modern mini-musical twist on 'Peter Pan' where kids will journey through Neverland, developing imagination, storytelling skills, and teamwork. The camp includes games, character creation, a talent show, and more. All levels are welcome, and family and friends can enjoy a mini-performance at the end of the week. Swim time may be available at Rec Center camps. No camp on July 4.

camp: Rec Center Music and Tech Camp
name: Theatre Camp
description: The Theatre Camp at Rec Center focuses on music, costumes, basic tech, and developing on-stage skills and teamwork for a special public performance. Teens aged 14 and above can participate in this camp, which meets on weekdays from 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. Participants are encouraged to bring a swimsuit and towel for a swim break. The camp culminates in a behind-the-scenes look at theatre production.
The performance program runs from 9am to 5pm, excluding July 4th, with the final day ending after a 7pm show. Participants can register and download camp forms from the FCPA website.

name: Camp Crescendo
description: Camp Crescendo offers fun, movement-based activities where children aged 6-12 years receive hands-on experience with a variety of instruments. This Rich Sandler music variety camp allows children to improvise, create, and learn fundamental skills to prepare them for future music lessons.

name: Ballet Dance Camp
description: Join us for a fun-filled Ballet Dance Camp where young dancers can learn and improve their ballet skills in a supportive and creative environment. This camp is designed for children aged 6-12 years old who have a passion for dance.

name: Rhythm and Movement
description: Participants in B2R Music Production Camp will engage in rhythm and movement activities culminating in a dance performance. The camp offers a behind-the-scenes look at the music industry and includes a swim break each afternoon. Participants are encouraged to bring a swimsuit and towel daily. The week concludes with a performance for family and friends.

name: Cheerleading Camp
description: This Skyhawks camp teaches young athletes the essential skills of cheers, proper hand/body movements, and jumping techniques. Campers will put on a performance at the end of the week.

name: Princess Ballet Camp
description: Campers learn ballet and creative movement with Envision Dance’s ballet camp. Every week, campers are encouraged to write their own songs or pick from over 400 popular arrangements. No music experience required. Camp does not run on July 4. Camps run the week of August 18 and 25 for non-FCPS participants. Depending on the skill level of the students, campers receive an award certificate.

camp: Fairfax County Park Authority Summer Camps
name: Megastar Dance Camp
description: Interpret movement with feelings. Learn lyrical, jumps, stunts, cheers, and a dance routine from former contemporary, hip-hop, and jazz using popular ballads. Build skills using contemporary music and the moves to dance on the balance beam, bars, floor, and vault.

name: Gymnastics & Dance Camp
description: Join Art in Motion to dance the week away with a whole week dedicated to America’s favorite popstar. Campers will learn dances and create Taylor-inspired crafts. The week will end with an energy-filled performance that includes gymnastics, rhythm-and-dance movement skills, games, and activities. Gymnastics apparatus included.

camp: Rec Center Music and Tech Camp
name: Tumbling Camp
description: The Tumbling Camp at Rec Center offers a fun and engaging program that includes tumbling, inflatable floor, bars, beam, and vault activities. Campers will also enjoy an after-noon swim break during the camp. A signed participation release is required. Join us for an exciting week of tumbling and gymnastics!

name: Adventures with Elsa & Anna
description: Immerse yourself in music and movement inspired by the Era Queen in this magical dance camp. Join Elsa, Anna, Kristoff, Olaf, and Sven as they embark on a new journey to find out more about Elsa’s powers in this magical dance camp. Through daily dance classes, participants will experience the magic of Elsa and Anna's world.

name: Foundational Dance Skills
description: Foundational Dance Skills program is filled with amazing new songs, timeless dance activities, beautiful costumes, and crafts. Campers will learn dance skills and prepare for a show on the last day.

camp: Rec Center Music and Tech Camp
name: Barbieland Dance Camp
description: Join Art in Motion for this glamorous new dance camp as we celebrate all things Barbie. Campers will learn new dance routines, create crafts, play games, and put on a performance at the end of the week.

name: Ninja Obstacles & Tumbling Camp
description: Be a ninja games warrior in this action-packed Metro Movement camp. Learn tumbling and have a chance to showcase all they learned throughout the week.

camp: Fairfax County Park Authority Summer Camps
Rec Center Music and Tech Camp
name: Envision Dance Camp
description: Campers will dance to the hottest music and dance styles in this Envision Dance camp as they play games and do arts and crafts. The camp includes an afternoon swim break. A signed participation release is due on the first day.

session: Learn about traveling careers. Create and trade sou-
description: This program offers moves and tumbling skills training by current and former UNwngtonFrst ES dancers, as well as NFL, NBA, collegiate, and other trained dancers. Participants will engage in skill-building activities from 9am to 4pm, with a focus on enhancing their dance techniques. The program includes an afternoon swim break for relaxation and fun. A signed participation release is required on the first day of camp.

name: Youth Technology Network camp
description: This Youth Technology Network camp offers a week-long program where participants will engage in activities such as making friendship bracelets and designing stage backdrops. All materials and equipment are provided for a creative and interactive experience.

name: Learn Now Music
description: Learn Now Music introduces campers to a variety of musical instruments and concepts including piano, guitar, violin, drums, voice, and movement.

name: Tumbling & Cheer Camp
description: Campers participate in musical games, crafts, listening excerpts, and related projects. Taught by former NFL, NBA, collegiate, and other trained cheerleaders and gymnasts, campers will enjoy tumbling and cheer activities. FREE instrument rentals are provided for in-camp use and at-home exploration (rental agreement must be signed).

name: Battle of the Bots
description: Gear up for an exciting robotics competition with iCODE! Design, build, and program your own robots using Vex Robotics. Campers will develop critical thinking and make their Minecraft blocks, film, animate effects, and do voice-overs.

camp: Snapology Robotics and Graphic Design Camp
name: LEGO® Robotics
description: In this exciting Snapology camp, designed for children aged 7-12 years old, participants will dive headfirst into the creativity of Minecraft and learn to design, build, and program their very own LEGO® creations. They will unlock the secrets of sensors, motors, and coding to bring their creations to life in a world of endless possibilities with Snapology.

camp: Second Sunday Craft Camp Adventure at the Woodlands
name: LEGO® Puzzles and Artistry
description: Unleash your inner artist and problem-solving skills as you tackle brain-teasing LEGO® puzzles. Dive into Backyard Science Camp to investigate the properties of water and air, experiment with bubbling concoctions, and learn about electricity. Whether you're a seasoned LEGO® master or a newcomer, this camp offers a unique opportunity to craft one-of-a-kind LEGO® masterpieces.

name: STEM Coding and Circuit Design
description: Campers will work with snap circuits, design engineering projects, and code in either Python or Scratch based on their grade levels. The program fosters creativity and critical thinking through hands-on projects. Previous participants will continue learning new STEM concepts.

name: Chemistry in the Kitchen
description: Chemistry in the Kitchen is a fun and educational program where kids get to explore the science behind cooking. Participants will engage in hands-on experiments and learn about chemical reactions in a kitchen setting.

location.address: Louise Archer Elementary School, [Full Address Here]

camp: Magic Sand and Science Secrets Camp
name: More Chemistry in the Kitchen
description: Explore chemistry in the kitchen with Science Seed's Doctors & Vets Camp. Discover the difference between baking soda and baking powder, and learn about the role yeast plays in pizza dough. The day is rounded out by outdoor recess, story time tied to the day’s science, and free reading.

name: Brain and Body Exploration
description: Join us at SteamKidz Lab's Exploration Camp where young participants aged 6-10 will have the opportunity to learn about the brain and body systems. Through hands-on activities like dissecting a model of the brain and studying the body's systems, campers will discover how reflexes work and gain insights into essential knowledge for aspiring doctors and veterinarians. Participants will engage in daily journal entries to document their discoveries.

camp: Rec Center Music and Tech Camp
name: Inventors and Construction Camp
description: Join us at the Inventors and Construction Camp where campers will explore the world of famous inventors, construction ingenuity, and hands-on building projects. Activities include building catapults and forts, creating a winning egg-drop design, constructing a dancing robot, and crafting a working light saber to take home. Campers will also learn about animals' senses, create a first aid kit for pets, and meet some animals. Don't forget to bring a lunch, snack, and drink for the day!

Join us at Adventure Camp for a week of exciting outdoor activities! Learn about crystals and blast a rocket into the air. Discover the states of matter and how things change with mixtures, solutions, and chemical reactions.

name: Introduction to Drones
description: Experience all aspects of drone technology in this hands-on camp. Participants will learn about drone mechanics, flight controls, safety measures, and have the opportunity to fly drones in a controlled environment. This camp is designed for children aged 7 to 12 years old.

location.address: Hidden Oaks Nature Center, 7701 Royce St, Annandale, VA

camp: nGREEN LOCATION CAMPS After School Program
name: It’s All About Science
description: Explore the wonders of science with hands-on experiments and activities. Learn about the nervous system, how germs enter the body, and various scientific topics including chemistry. Other activities include outdoor recess, science-related story time, and daily journaling. This program is designed for children aged 6-10 years.

name: Biology and Physics Fun Camp
